Author: cah5896#7669
Content: https://cryptoslate.com/cnbcs-brian-kelly-bitcoin-will-resurrect/amp/ is an example of mainstream media positivity. I feel like "bitcoin is dead" people have mostly been fringe CEOs that know nothing about the technology lately and not journalists and large media outlets. Bitcointalk speculation section isn't close to as doom and gloom as the 2015 lows. We didn't have a Mt. Gox like incident this year, but the charts are highly similar. I don't know which of those are bullish and which are bearish. Guess I'm a contrarian usually. This stock market has to come down at some point, the fundamentals don't add up. KMD can't stay at 60th forever; that is ridiculous undervaluation.

Author: Jazzy#0001
Content: You highlight some good points. People who were around in 2014 have said again and again how fundamentally things have changed vs today. Back then they had no idea if something like Gox could have meant the end for bitcoin and the suicide hotline was pinned on reddit, but we've been through so much since then and now we know that nothing so far has managed to kill bitcoin and nothing on the horizon even has a chance.
